    "The inclusion of their results does not undermine the fairness or outcome of the comparison.",
    "Please refer to Appendix B.3 for the implementation details.",
    "It is noteworthy that RED surpassed the prompt tuning (PT) baseline with a significant margin of 11.9% on average.",
    "Despite PT methods necessitating the fewest parameters during fine-tuning among other PEFT baselines, they still require a modification of parameters that is twice as large as that required by RED.",
    "This finding indicates that allocating a few number of learnable parameters to each layer for representation editing is both more parameter-efficient and effective compared to the PT method, which assigns all learnable parameters to the model's embedding layer."
